Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.12,0:00:22.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,既然你们开着沙滩车\N{\fs90}Since you're in beach buggies,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.62,0:00:24.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,你们将驶向沙滩\N{\fs90}you will now drive to the beach
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.45,0:00:26.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,北上到纳米比亚最北\N{\fs90}at the northernmost point
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.15,0:00:28.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,和安哥拉的交界处\N{\fs90}of Namibia, where it meets Angola.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.22,0:00:31.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,全程1600公里\N{\fs90}It's 1,000 miles away.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.33,0:00:33.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们一定要找到这条路\N{\fs90}We have got to find this road.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.16,0:00:36.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,在黑暗里这么开下去太冒险\N{\fs90}This is not gonna be too clever in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.70,0:00:40.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,我一定会找到南十字星\N{\fs90}Listen. I shall find the Southern Cross.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.60,0:00:43.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,这主意真蠢\N{\fs90}Oh, this is a bad idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.17,0:00:44.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们把性命交在一只猩猩的手里\N{\fs90}We are now trusting our lives
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.74,0:00:47.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,而这只猩猩又以为自己是帕特里克 穆尔\N{\fs90}to an orangutang who thinks he's Patrick Moore.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.21,0:00:50.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,整整24小时 又冰冷又悲惨\N{\fs90}24 hours of cold, misery,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.01,0:00:53.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,结果又回到原点\N{\fs90}to achieve exactly nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.18,0:00:55.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,真的一事无成\N{\fs90}I mean, it is exactly nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.19,0:00:58.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,海水涨过来了\N{\fs90}Oh, it's coming in!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.22,0:01:03.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是我走过的最诱人的沙漠\N{\fs90}This is the best desert I've ever been to.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.69,0:01:05.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,我勒个槽\N{\fs90}Holy shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.90,0:01:14.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,它实际是个庞大的橙色杀人机器\N{\fs90}What it actually is is a big, orange killing engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.17,0:01:16.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,妈呀\N{\fs90}- Jesus!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.14,0:01:18.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,老天爷\N{\fs90}Oh, my God!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.37,0:01:21.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,求求你 开上去吧\N{\fs90}Please make it! Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.85,0:01:29.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,真的需要找到路了 这可很严肃了\N{\fs90}Just need to find a road now. This is not funny any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.35,0:01:31.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,不想再在沙漠里过夜\N{\fs90}I don't want another night in the desert.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.15,0:01:33.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,谢天谢地\N{\fs90}Oh, my God.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.52,0:01:35.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,可以向东 可以向西\N{\fs90}I could go east, I could go west.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.59,0:01:37.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,不管去哪儿都有路\N{\fs90}Whichever way you go, it goes somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.79,0:01:41.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,通向自由的大路\N{\fs90}Yes! It is the road to freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.33,0:01:43.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,什么鬼东西\N{\fs90}What the hell was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.74,0:01:51.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,我在开的 至少在试着开的 真是阿波罗13号\N{\fs90}What I'm driving here, or attempting to drive, is Apollo 13.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.78,0:02:02.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,等到早上 我才把伤势惨烈的座驾蹭到温得和克\N{\fs90}It was morning by the time I nursed my wounded car into Windhoek,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.95,0:02:06.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,而我吃好睡好的败类同事们\N{\fs90}and my well-rested colleagues were full of admiration
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.19,0:02:08.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,对我的壮举充满了崇拜\N{\fs90}for how I'd pulled off such a feat.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.62,0:02:11.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这是你的第一方案么  -怎么了\N{\fs90}-Is that the first thing you thought of? - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.79,0:02:14.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,就拆了一个洞 这能有啥用\N{\fs90}Tear a hole in it. What's that gonna do?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.23,0:02:17.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,我要够着散热器那的引气活门 在那儿\N{\fs90}I needed to get to the bleed valve on the radiator, which is there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.80,0:02:20.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,-继续说  -这还不算 还有更倒霉的\N{\fs90}- Is it? - And, to make life doubly difficult...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.07,0:02:24.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,我把我眼镜片给踩了\N{\fs90}...I trod on my spectacles.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.74,0:02:27.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,也太杯具了 单眼兽当修车师傅\N{\fs90}That is tragic, trying to fix it with one lens.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.71,0:02:31.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,我试着修车 而且我只会闭右眼\N{\fs90}I was trying to fix it. And the only eye I can close is this eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.75,0:02:34.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,-左眼闭不上么  -闭不上\N{\fs90}-You can't close your left eye? -I can't close my left eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.38,0:02:38.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,你怎么不把眼镜倒过来 那样右眼就能用了\N{\fs90}Why didn't you put them on upside down? You'd have the lens over the other eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.26,0:02:42.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,神逻辑\N{\fs90}That is logic there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.56,0:02:44.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,说得有理\N{\fs90}Oh, yeah
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.69,0:02:47.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,-好吧 上路吧 今天要赶路  -慢着\N{\fs90}- Come on, let's go. We've got a lot to do. - JEREMY: No!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.46,0:02:49.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们目前唯一得到的教训就是\N{\fs90}The one thing we have established now is that,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.66,0:02:51.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,除了首都温得和克\N{\fs90}with the exception of Windhoek,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.43,0:02:56.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,纳米比亚的土地步步维艰\N{\fs90}which is the capital, Namibia is a tough and arduous place.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.30,0:02:57.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,-有理  -你买了地图吗\N{\fs90}- Yeah. - Have you bought maps?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.04,0:03:00.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,你有任何宿营设施吗\N{\fs90}- No. - Have you got tenting equipment of any sort?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.81,0:03:04.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,除了躺沙子上 你想好了沙漠露营地吗 都没有\N{\fs90}Have you got somewhere to sleep other than the desert floor? No.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.35,0:03:07.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,要我说 今天我们养精蓄锐\N{\fs90}So why don't we, today, get prepared
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.42,0:03:10.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,为了下段旅程 一大段旅程做准备\N{\fs90}for the next leg of the - big leg of the journey?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.79,0:03:13.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,-好主意  -那就这样定了\N{\fs90}- That is a good idea. We'll do that. - That's not a bad idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.49,0:03:16.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们给自己奖励购物一天\N{\fs90}We'll grant ourselves a day of... shopping. Mm.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.92,0:03:20.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,不过首先 请容我一刻\N{\fs90}First of all, would you permit me to chisel some of the cheddar
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.76,0:03:23.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,把裤衩里捂出来的百虫千菌清一清\N{\fs90}that has grown in my underpants away?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.27,0:03:24.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,你别在这儿干\N{\fs90}Well, not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.13,0:03:28.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,在刮干净我的器官后\N{\fs90}Having de-cheesed my body parts,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.67,0:03:32.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们去搞一些必要的物资\N{\fs90}we headed out to get the necessary supplies.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.57,0:03:34.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,问题是 如果我们用网眼布材料\N{\fs90}The thing is, if we go mesh,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.04,0:03:37.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,网眼挡太阳但是不挡光\N{\fs90}it'll keep the sun off but it won't keep the light out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.88,0:03:40.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,有光睡不了懒觉 而且它重1.5公斤 但\N{\fs90}That will wake us up early. That's 1.5 kilograms. But--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.35,0:03:44.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德 在我们血拼之前你一定要明白\N{\fs90}Hammond, the first thing you need to know before we start shopping in here
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.59,0:03:47.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,我和船长俩人说算\N{\fs90}is James and I are in charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.09,0:03:49.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,对不住 不过你不说算\N{\fs90}Well... - JAMES: Sorry, he's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.09,0:03:51.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,你们做不了主意 因为你们对宿营一无所知\N{\fs90}No, you're not. You don't know anything about camping.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.29,0:03:53.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,-正因为如此  -那么干嘛要拿主意\N{\fs90}- JAMES, JEREMY: Exactly. - How does that make you in charge?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.33,0:03:55.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为我们清楚宿营很糟糕\N{\fs90}Because we know it's all terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.43,0:03:59.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果你说了算 我们最后得会在小迷彩三角袋里过夜\N{\fs90}If we leave it to you, we'll all end up sleeping in small green triangles.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.07,0:04:01.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,你对野外宿营的概念是在湖畔\N{\fs90}The camping you know about is in the Lake District,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.50,0:04:04.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,故意过悲惨野人生活\N{\fs90}where you deliberately make yourself miserable.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.31,0:04:05.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,对不起 不过他一点没错\N{\fs90}I'm sorry, he's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.34,0:04:08.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,依我所见\N{\fs90}It is possible, I think,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.44,0:04:10.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,只有才华和金钱\N{\fs90}with a bit of ingenuity and money,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.71,0:04:12.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,才能让露营至少可以忍受\N{\fs90}to make tenting bearable.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.08,0:04:16.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,童子军哈蒙德并不认同\N{\fs90}Richard Baden-Hammond disagreed,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.75,0:04:19.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以我们就地解散\N{\fs90}so we went our separate ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.55,0:04:21.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,正确 错误\N{\fs90}Correct, incorrect.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.46,0:04:23.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,-没错 -同意吗\N{\fs90}- Exactly. - Do you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.09,0:04:24.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我这有个更正确的  -赞\N{\fs90}- But I'd go even more correct. - Oh, yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.86,0:04:28.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,完美 在沙子上这样卷开\N{\fs90}Perfect. Roll it out on the desert floor...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.33,0:04:31.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,像到家了一样\N{\fs90}...you're home.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.37,0:04:33.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯 我找到酷彩锅了\N{\fs90}Oh, James! Le Creuset!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.50,0:04:36.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德会恨死这玩意 它比帐篷还重\N{\fs90}See, Hammond would hate this, because this weighs more than a tent.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.90,0:04:39.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,-确实重  -重很多\N{\fs90}- Which it does, actually. - A lot more.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.11,0:04:42.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,-高重量 高质量  -真理\N{\fs90}- And it weighs more because it is a quality item. - Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.51,0:04:44.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,便携泥铲\N{\fs90}Pocket trowel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.85,0:04:45.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,便携香皂\N{\fs90}Pocket soap.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.95,0:04:48.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,这才像话\N{\fs90}Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.35,0:04:51.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,-意面匙  -好主意\N{\fs90}- Pasta spoon. - Yeah, good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.49,0:04:54.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,这个开瓶器有点.. 太轻了\N{\fs90}I find that bottle opener a bit... lightweight.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.52,0:04:56.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们要找更烧钱的\N{\fs90}Yeah, more expensive is what we're looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.42,0:04:58.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,船长 过来看\N{\fs90}You see, look at this, James.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.26,0:05:00.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德会把这种破玩意儿当成椅子\N{\fs90}This is the sort of thing Hammond would think is a chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.90,0:05:06.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是必备 一个灶炉就搞定了\N{\fs90}Ooh! That's all you need. That's your whole... stove.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.13,0:05:07.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,这就够了\N{\fs90}That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.70,0:05:09.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这是燃气灶吧  -应该是\N{\fs90}- Is it gas? It is, isn't it? - I presume so.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.97,0:05:13.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,两个灶炉 能塞个小鸡了 野鸡也行\N{\fs90}For two, you could get a small chicken in there, or... a pheasant.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.61,0:05:15.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,差不多了\N{\fs90}We're getting there now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.65,0:05:19.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,可以这样折叠\N{\fs90}So that folds down to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.82,0:05:24.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,不错\N{\fs90}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.09,0:05:29.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,第二天清晨 我们重新上路\N{\fs90}The next morning, we headed out once more,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.89,0:05:32.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯和我采买的\N{\fs90}with the camping gear James and I had bought
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.66,0:05:34.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,露营物资随后跟车\N{\fs90}bringing up the rear.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.00,0:05:40.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,购买物资之余\N{\fs90}And besides stocking up with essentials,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.50,0:05:46.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,我和哈蒙德还在首都休整时改装了车\N{\fs90}Hammond and I had used our day off in Windhoek to modify our cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.87,0:05:50.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,为了改善发动机过热 我装了个集风进气铲\N{\fs90}To solve my overheating problems, I've fitted a ram-air scoop,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.45,0:05:55.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,开车时 会把凉风铲进散热器\N{\fs90}which shovels refreshing, cooling air into the radiator as I go along.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.28,0:05:59.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且你可能看到了 我装了一个风翼\N{\fs90}And, as you may have noticed, I've fitted a spoiler.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.89,0:06:05.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的沙滩车对我来说唯一的不足\N{\fs90}My only complaint, really, about my beach buggy
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.79,0:06:08.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是在3档和4档动力不够\N{\fs90}was its lack of performance in third and fourth gears.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.03,0:06:11.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,没法给发动机加动力 不想给引擎压力\N{\fs90}Couldn't up power from the engine and I don't want to stress it,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.60,0:06:13.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,不过我可以给车减肥\N{\fs90}so I could lighten it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.44,0:06:16.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,我把这里的顶架去掉 扔掉了副驾驶座椅\N{\fs90}I've stripped away the superstructure here and the passenger seat,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.00,0:06:18.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,不必要的该删就删\N{\fs90}anything spare.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.97,0:06:24.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,结果就是 这辆车轻了三四十公斤\N{\fs90}That means this car is 30-40 kilos lighter than it was before.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.81,0:06:29.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,杰里米 你的车怎么长出了土绿的八字胡\N{\fs90}Jeremy, why has your car sprouted a green moustache?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.25,0:06:32.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,是个风翼 为了给车头增加下压力\N{\fs90}Well, it's a spoiler for added downforce at the front end,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.02,0:06:35.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,后置引擎车很需要\N{\fs90}which you need in a rear-engine vehicle.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.69,0:06:38.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,这辆车现在过弯能力惊人\N{\fs90}This thing will be unbelievable through the corners now,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.89,0:06:40.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,不骗你\N{\fs90}it really will.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.13,0:06:41.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,和保时捷911没两样\N{\fs90}Like a 911.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.53,0:06:43.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,我跟你说\N{\fs90}And I tell you what,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.90,0:06:45.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,就算你的超轻沙滩车\N{\fs90}even with your new lightweight buggy,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.90,0:06:49.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,和我现在的座驾相比 也只能后面吃灰\N{\fs90}you're no match for what I've got here this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.60,0:06:52.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,不好意思 我的车更快\N{\fs90}Yeah, I'm sorry, mate. This is quicker.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.47,0:06:54.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,-瞎说  -才没\N{\fs90}- It is not. - It is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.88,0:06:58.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 哈蒙德 我向你挑战\N{\fs90}Right, Richard Hammond, I challenge you to a race.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.15,0:07:00.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,战就战 谁怕谁  大白痴\N{\fs90}OK, you're on. Idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.82,0:07:03.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们找个赛道 去赛车\N{\fs90}We shall find a race track and we shall do racing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.82,0:07:06.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,你们玩你们的 我才不赛车\N{\fs90}Well, you carry on. I'm not doing any racing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.29,0:07:08.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,一点意义也没有\N{\fs90}That's utterly pointless.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.06,0:07:12.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,在市郊\N{\fs90}On the outskirts of the city,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.16,0:07:14.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们找到了一个不错的赛道\N{\fs90}we found a rather excellent circuit
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.36,0:07:16.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,在这里 我们可以跑圈计时\N{\fs90}where we could do timed laps,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.66,0:07:20.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯可以玩玩他新买的吸尘器\N{\fs90}and James could try out his new vacuum cleaner.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.20,0:07:22.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,爽歪歪\N{\fs90}Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.41,0:07:26.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,-准备好没  -不行\N{\fs90}- Are you ready? - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.81,0:07:29.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你干嘛  -要等水温和胎压\N{\fs90}- Why not? - Temperatures and pressures.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.71,0:07:31.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,这可是赛道神器 看看它\N{\fs90}This is a racing machine. Look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.98,0:07:34.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,不过是塑料沙滩车 停在V8旁边\N{\fs90}It's a plastic beach buggy parked near a V8.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.62,0:07:36.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,-还有空力套件  -少来\N{\fs90}- With aero. - Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.55,0:07:38.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,各就各位\N{\fs90}- In...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.15,0:07:40.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,.3 2 1 起步\N{\fs90}..three, two, one, go!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.66,0:07:44.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,得让我挂上档\N{\fs90}Yeah, I'm gonna do it in gear.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.23,0:07:46.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,-再试试  -让我再试试\N{\fs90}- Give it a shot. - I'm gonna try that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.36,0:07:48.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,-各就各位  -不行 油门卡死了\N{\fs90}- In-- - No! Throttle's jammed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.30,0:07:52.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,-还是卡着的  -各就各位\N{\fs90}- Jammed. - In--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.43,0:07:54.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,停 这破油门\N{\fs90}No! You can keep saying "in"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.40,0:07:55.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,你说 各就各位 说到天黑也没用\N{\fs90}till the cows come home. The throttle...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.08,0:08:03.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,3 2 1 走起\N{\fs90}Three, two, one, begin!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.79,0:08:13.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,怎么停下了\N{\fs90}Why... Why have you stopped?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.72,0:08:18.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,油门又收不回来了\N{\fs90}The throttle may have gone a bit open.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.63,0:08:24.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,油门完全报废\N{\fs90}My throttle is totally broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.77,0:08:26.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,-话说回来 哈蒙德  -啥事\N{\fs90}- Anyway, Hammond... - Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.77,0:08:29.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,任何起步能前轮飞起的车\N{\fs90}Any car which can wheelie off the line...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.94,0:08:32.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,击败你都完全没问题\N{\fs90}is going to be able to beat yours, and would have done.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.57,0:08:33.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,不好意思 打断你\N{\fs90}So... Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.04,0:08:35.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,你是说 你的车刚开跑\N{\fs90}You're saying because your car started,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.81,0:08:37.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,没跑50米就坏了\N{\fs90}well, 50 yards away over there,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.75,0:08:39.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,前轮飞起 失控 砸下来\N{\fs90}wheelied, was uncontrollable, slammed back down
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.78,0:08:41.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,趴窝 这就是赛道神器么\N{\fs90}and broke itself, it's the best on the track?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.02,0:08:43.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,没错\N{\fs90}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.45,0:08:46.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,长知识了 真实用 多亏这比赛\N{\fs90}Well, much learned. Really useful. Glad we did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.69,0:08:53.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,等杰里米把不断出状况的车修好\N{\fs90}With Jeremy's endlessly troublesome car fixed again,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.46,0:08:57.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们没收了詹姆斯的戴森 继续向北\N{\fs90}we scooped up James' Dyson and continued northwards
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.13,0:09:00.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,向安哥拉边境前进\N{\fs90}towards the finish line at the border with Angola.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.61,0:09:07.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,一路上 风顺 路平 不同寻常地安静\N{\fs90}The going was smooth and easy and eerily quiet,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.91,0:09:10.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,这就奇怪了\N{\fs90}which begged a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.31,0:09:15.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,据说纳米比亚是世界上开车最危险的地方\N{\fs90}Now, apparently, Namibia is the most dangerous place in the world to drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.38,0:09:17.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,这里的人均事故率比其它地方都高\N{\fs90}There are more accidents per head then anywhere else,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.95,0:09:20.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且 在青年人口中\N{\fs90}and car accidents are the first
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.79,0:09:24.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,车祸是造成死亡最大的诱因\N{\fs90}and most common cause of death in young adults.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.36,0:09:27.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,为什么 这怎么可能\N{\fs90}How? How can that be so?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.63,0:09:29.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,你看 这里万里无人\N{\fs90}I mean... the place is empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.64,0:09:39.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,在英国 平均每平方公里有250-260人\N{\fs90}In Britain, there are 250-260 people for every square kilometre.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.84,0:09:42.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,在这里 平均只有2人\N{\fs90}Here... it's two.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.18,0:09:45.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,两个人\N{\fs90}Two!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.11,0:09:48.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,与这相比 澳大利亚的荒漠像是摩纳哥一样热闹\N{\fs90}This makes the Australian outback look like Monaco.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.38,0:09:50.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,有猴子\N{\fs90}Monkey! Monkey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.92,0:09:54.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,屁眼超大 你们看到了吗\N{\fs90}Huge anus! Did you see that thing's anus?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.82,0:09:58.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,与此同时\N{\fs90}I, however, was not thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.56,0:10:01.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,我想的不是人口数和猴臀\N{\fs90}about population statistics or monkeys' bottoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.90,0:10:04.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,我只是庆幸终于开在了平路上\N{\fs90}I was just happy to be on a smooth surface
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.80,0:10:08.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且车里不再遍布灰尘\N{\fs90}in a car that wasn't filled with dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.10,0:10:09.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,轻松上阵\N{\fs90}I shall relax...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.41,0:10:12.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,风景迷人\N{\fs90}...with the lovely view.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.21,0:10:17.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,不幸地是 几里路之后\N{\fs90}Sadly, though, a few miles later...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.31,0:10:22.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,嗷嗷嗷 我的蛋蛋啊\N{\fs90}Ow! Ow! Oh, my nuts! Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.55,0:10:28.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,别闹了\N{\fs90}Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.66,0:10:31.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯梅\N{\fs90}James May?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.29,0:10:33.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,我能听到 我太不爽了\N{\fs90}Yes, I can hear you, but it's very uncomfortable
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.96,0:10:36.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的车也 说坏就坏了\N{\fs90}and my car has... has cut out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.21,0:10:46.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯很幸运\N{\fs90}Mercifully for James,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.27,0:10:48.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们开到了野生动物保护区\N{\fs90}we eventually arrived at a game reserve,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.28,0:10:51.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们决定这里是理想的\N{\fs90}which we decided would be an ideal place
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.11,0:10:54.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,过夜宿营地\N{\fs90}to set up camp for the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.25,0:11:01.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,这就够了\N{\fs90}That's what we need.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.72,0:11:04.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,一边是哈蒙德搭建帆布小破屋\N{\fs90}As Hammond built his canvas hovel...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.06,0:11:11.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,我和詹姆斯期待着更文明的夜晚\N{\fs90}...James and I were looking forward to a more civilised evening
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.83,0:11:13.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,就在我们顺带买来的管家\N{\fs90}in the tents we'd bought,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.20,0:11:15.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,为我们建起来\N{\fs90}and which had been erected
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.07,0:11:17.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,过夜帐篷里\N{\fs90}by the butler we'd also bought.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.91,0:11:20.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,多谢 乔瓦尼\N{\fs90}Thank you, Giovanni.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.78,0:11:24.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,把你衬衫塞裤子里 这不是房车旅行\N{\fs90}Tuck your shirt in, man! It's not a bloody caravan site.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.78,0:11:27.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,我在想 晚餐\N{\fs90}Erm... I'm just thinking, dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.28,0:11:29.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,我先去换件衣服行不行\N{\fs90}Mm. Do you mind if I get changed?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.28,0:11:31.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,我也要去冲个澡\N{\fs90}- No, exactly. I'm gonna have a shower. - Mm.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.05,0:11:34.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,-去泡个澡吧  -真心赞\N{\fs90}- Or I may have a bath, actually. - Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.86,0:11:37.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,乔瓦尼 去把热水准备了\N{\fs90}Giovanni, could you run the baths?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.90,0:11:48.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,据说这家餐厅还有牡蛎\N{\fs90}Apparently, this place has got oysters.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.77,0:11:51.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,-是么 在这还有  -可说是呢 多厉害\N{\fs90}- Really? Here? - Yeah. I know, it's extraordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.57,0:11:52.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,谁能想到咧\N{\fs90}Who knew?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.01,0:11:54.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,来共进晚餐吗\N{\fs90}Are you coming for some dinner?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.94,0:11:57.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,你什么意思 共进晚餐 我都在这儿做好了\N{\fs90}What do you mean, "Coming for dinner"? I'm cooking here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.38,0:11:58.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,那里有一家餐厅\N{\fs90}There's a restaurant just down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.81,0:12:00.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,-餐厅  -没错 就在前面\N{\fs90}- A restaurant? - Yeah, just down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.31,0:12:02.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,我不想去\N{\fs90}I don't want to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.28,0:12:03.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,我在这里正经露营\N{\fs90}I'm cooking this. I'm doing it properly, camping.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.05,0:12:05.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你就来 -餐后我来找你们\N{\fs90}- Well, come and-- - I'll join you after dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.79,0:12:07.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,随你吧\N{\fs90}Whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.19,0:12:08.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,他整个一土老汉\N{\fs90}He's such a peasant, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.62,0:12:10.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,太不可思议了\N{\fs90}It's just unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.59,0:12:12.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,晚饭时\N{\fs90}That evening in the restaurant,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.99,0:12:14.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德并没有加入我们\N{\fs90}Hammond never did join us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.03,0:12:18.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,不过我和詹姆斯却不孤单\N{\fs90}But James and I were not short of company.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.43,0:12:22.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,看 有犀牛 真犀牛哎\N{\fs90}Oh, look, there's rhinos! There's actual rhinos!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.20,0:12:24.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,它们的牛角已经被拔了\N{\fs90}And they've been dehorned.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.81,0:12:25.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,为了防止偷猎者射杀犀牛\N{\fs90}They've had to take its horn out
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.87,0:12:28.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,才把牛角摘除\N{\fs90}to stop poachers shooting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.11,0:12:30.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,不过你知道偷猎者现在会干出什么事来吗\N{\fs90}But you know what the poachers are doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.01,0:12:32.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们也会杀牛角摘除过的犀牛\N{\fs90}They shoot the dehorned ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.61,0:12:35.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们会跟踪一只犀牛 跟踪几天\N{\fs90}because if they track for a couple of days, a rhino,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.92,0:12:37.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果发现犀牛没有角 就把它射掉\N{\fs90}and then it's got no horn, they shoot it,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.72,0:12:41.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,以后就不用再跟踪同一只犀牛了 节省时间\N{\fs90}and then they'll never track it again, so it saves time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.26,0:12:43.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,你知道现在犀牛角什么价吗\N{\fs90}Do you know how much you get for a rhino horn now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.99,0:12:46.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,-在黑市场上吗  -对 比如在越南\N{\fs90}- On the... On the market? - Yeah, in Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.66,0:12:47.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,我敢猜是一大笔钱\N{\fs90}I'm guessing it's a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.86,0:12:50.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,32万美金\N{\fs90}$320,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.70,0:12:53.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,-比金条还值钱  -老天爷啊\N{\fs90}- So that's more expensive than gold. - Good God.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.40,0:12:57.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,就连这只犀牛上还留下的那个小瘤\N{\fs90}Even the nub that's left that he's got is still worth,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.17,0:12:58.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,我估计也值几千美金\N{\fs90}I don't know, thousands of dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.84,0:13:00.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,我正要说 不论多细致地除角\N{\fs90}I was gonna say, no matter how carefully you dehorn it,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.98,0:13:04.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,还是会有一点遗留在鼻子里面\N{\fs90}there's still horn going down into its nose.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.08,0:13:08.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这太令人寒心了  -可说是的\N{\fs90}- JEREMY: That's such a tragedy, that, you know. - JAMES: Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.32,0:13:10.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,我想我们既然来了 就做点贡献\N{\fs90}I want to do something about this while we're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.55,0:13:12.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,一定可以想出解决办法的\N{\fs90}I'm sure we could come up with something.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.89,0:13:15.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,一定可以\N{\fs90}I'm sure we could.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.20,0:13:29.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,第二天清晨 天一亮我就被征兵\N{\fs90}RICHARD: The next morning, I woke to find I'd been recruited
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.77,0:13:34.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,进了克拉克森和梅犀牛保护小队\N{\fs90}into the Clarkson and May Rhino Protection Squad.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.51,0:13:36.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们俩居然一口咬定\N{\fs90}They were even convinced that our beach buggies
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.78,0:13:41.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们的沙滩车是跟踪偷猎者的首选车辆\N{\fs90}would be ideal for tracking the poachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.65,0:13:44.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,不可否认 他们说的犀牛问题有道理\N{\fs90}I can't deny, they do have a point about the whole rhino thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.89,0:13:46.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,简直荒谬\N{\fs90}It is ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.42,0:13:49.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,在非洲 平均每天都有两只犀牛被射杀\N{\fs90}Two rhinos killed every day in Africa by poachers,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.89,0:13:54.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,被卖给黑市 因为有人迷信\N{\fs90}and then sold to a market that believes it's a cure for cancer,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.63,0:13:56.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,犀牛角能治癌症 阳痿 甚至宿醉\N{\fs90}impotence, even hangovers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.03,0:14:00.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,不过要正面解决这个大问题\N{\fs90}But are we necessarily the right men
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.53,0:14:03.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们几个是最佳人选么\N{\fs90}to tackle it head-on in the field?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.34,0:14:10.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,在超市里捐献个一块钱\N{\fs90}Wouldn't we be better just popping a £1 coin in a jar
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.28,0:14:14.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,让专家来解决问题 岂不是更有效\N{\fs90}and letting somebody who knows what they're doing solve it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.55,0:14:16.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,从昨天住宿的地方\N{\fs90}Well, I've got a tranquilizer gun
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.35,0:14:18.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,我拿了支麻醉枪\N{\fs90}from the place where we were last night, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.45,0:14:22.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,但我找不到谁能当靶子\N{\fs90}...I can't see anyone to shoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.96,0:14:29.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,估计偷猎者是不会用大路\N{\fs90}Figuring that the poachers probably didn't use the main road,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.70,0:14:32.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,于是我们驶进了树丛里寻找\N{\fs90}we went off to look in the bush.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.93,0:14:34.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,那边怎么样\N{\fs90}What about over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.97,0:14:38.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,没有偷猎者\N{\fs90}No poachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.64,0:14:41.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,这里有轮胎记\N{\fs90}Tyre marks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.04,0:14:44.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,可能会是偷猎者\N{\fs90}It may be some poacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.65,0:14:45.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,不对\N{\fs90}Oh, no, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.85,0:14:48.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,百路驰轮胎 这是詹姆斯的胎记\N{\fs90}BF Goodriches. This is James May.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.19,0:14:53.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,你给我听着 我们这事儿太蠢了\N{\fs90}Just so you know, this is stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.42,0:14:55.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,怎么蠢了\N{\fs90}What's stupid?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.49,0:14:57.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,你怎么能认出来偷猎者\N{\fs90}How would you recognise a poacher when you saw one?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.79,0:15:01.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,-就算你找到了 又能把他怎么样  -射他\N{\fs90}- And when you find one, what are you gonna do? - Shoot him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.23,0:15:02.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,这次旅程唯一的目的\N{\fs90}All we're doing on our journey
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.00,0:15:05.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,只是开三辆沙滩车到安哥拉边境\N{\fs90}is driving three beach buggies to the Angolan border.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.80,0:15:07.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,-没错  -这对人类社会没什么贡献\N{\fs90}- Yeah. - Which doesn't further the cause of humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.83,0:15:09.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,-说得对  -这么转悠着就有贡献了么\N{\fs90}- Exactly. - And this does, does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.57,0:15:13.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德 我们有一天时间 给我们24小时\N{\fs90}We've got a day, Hammond. Give us 24 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.81,0:15:17.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,就一天 之后我们保证重新再上路\N{\fs90}24 hours. Then, I promise, we'll get back on the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.78,0:15:24.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,持怀疑态度的队友让步之后\N{\fs90}JEREMY: Once our sceptical colleague had agreed,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.75,0:15:26.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,我决定改变策略\N{\fs90}I decided to change tack,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.79,0:15:30.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,放弃陆路 从空中搜索\N{\fs90}abandon the cars and search from the air,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.26,0:15:33.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,借用些沙漠滑翔帆伞设备\N{\fs90}using some beach-front parasailing equipment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.83,0:15:37.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,-杰里米  -啥事\N{\fs90}- Jeremy? - Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.40,0:15:40.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果我们活不回来 你记住 我恨死你了\N{\fs90}If we don't make it, please know that I hate you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.33,0:15:43.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,连一丝风都没有 别犯傻了\N{\fs90}There's not a breath of wind, so don't be stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.01,0:15:46.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,哎呀 我的降落伞\N{\fs90}Oh, my parachute's been...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.01,0:15:50.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,-不妙  -拜拜了您呐\N{\fs90}- Oh, hello! - Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.04,0:15:52.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,屎啊\N{\fs90}Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.02,0:15:58.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,搞栽了\N{\fs90}That's not worked at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.45,0:16:00.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 我不敢这么玩命了\N{\fs90}OK. Right, I'm not gonna do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.02,0:16:04.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,很显然 我的策略太危险了\N{\fs90}Clearly, my solution was too dangerous for us,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.46,0:16:07.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,于是我们把乔瓦尼送了上去\N{\fs90}so we sent Giovanni up instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.53,0:16:11.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,看 他飞远了 马上就会坠下来死掉\N{\fs90}Look, he's going over there. He's gonna crash and die.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.70,0:16:15.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,-他只是被风吹歪了  -而且要吹掉下来了\N{\fs90}- No, he's been blown a bit sideways but-- - And downwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.70,0:16:19.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,他自己没同意吧\N{\fs90}He didn't sign up for this, did he?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.31,0:16:24.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,乔瓦尼没找到任何偷猎者\N{\fs90}Giovanni failed to spot any poachers,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.21,0:16:26.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以我们让他别再胡搞了\N{\fs90}so we told him to stop messing about
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.31,0:16:28.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,回到营地里给我们倒酒\N{\fs90}and get back to camp to pour some drinks,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.05,0:16:32.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,这时 我们集体反思\N{\fs90}whilst we had a rethink.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.15,0:16:34.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们所有的计划都没成功\N{\fs90}Everything we've tried has gone wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.06,0:16:37.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,承认失败 继续前行吧\N{\fs90}So let's accept it now and move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.62,0:16:38.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,抓紧赶路\N{\fs90}We can go.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.06,0:16:40.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,不干\N{\fs90}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.43,0:16:44.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,我估计偷猎者只会在晚上出来偷猎\N{\fs90}I think the poachers only go out at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.60,0:16:46.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,你丫真狠\N{\fs90}Oh, for God's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.10,0:16:47.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们等太阳下山了\N{\fs90}We'll let the sun set,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.80,0:16:49.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,找来先进的战术装备\N{\fs90}get some tactical kit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.67,0:16:52.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,-手持步枪  -来玩吧 哈蒙德\N{\fs90}- Rifles. - Come on, Hammond.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.87,0:16:55.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,你说给我们24小时 之后才要我们缴枪呢\N{\fs90}You gave us 24 hours before you took our guns and badges.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.54,0:16:57.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,-他的确说过  -行吧\N{\fs90}- He did. -  OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.48,0:17:01.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,再整几瓶啤的 然后就去耍\N{\fs90}I think a couple more beers, head out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.45,0:17:02.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,赞\N{\fs90}I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.98,0:17:04.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,-耐心点 等到天黑  -对的\N{\fs90}- Let it get dark. Be patient. - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.82,0:17:07.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,-捕猎者都需要耐心  -当然\N{\fs90}- Hunters are patient, aren't they? - Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.73,0:17:14.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,等到一片漆黑\N{\fs90}JEREMY: Once darkness had fallen,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.76,0:17:16.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们开始行动\N{\fs90}we got kitted out
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.10,0:17:18.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,手持麻醉枪 身穿武装衣\N{\fs90}with tranquilizer guns and tactical kit
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.27,0:17:19.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,带着没信心的哈蒙德\N{\fs90}and headed back into the bush
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.87,0:17:24.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,重新回到了树丛中\N{\fs90}with a very unsure Richard in tow.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.61,0:17:26.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,我不是不想阻止偷猎\N{\fs90}I mean, I'd like to stop poachers,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.54,0:17:31.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,不过晚上在这里 偷猎者和狮子的比例是多少\N{\fs90}but out here at night, what is the poacher-to-lion ratio?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.18,0:17:33.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,两者中 我更会遇到哪一个\N{\fs90}What am I more likely to find?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.72,0:17:39.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,必要的策略是跟随犀牛脚印\N{\fs90}What you have to do is look for rhino tracks,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.75,0:17:43.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为偷猎者也会这样跟踪犀牛\N{\fs90}cos that's what the poachers will be following.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.51,0:18:01.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,真是一生中做过的最男子汉的事情\N{\fs90}Literally the most manly thing I've ever done.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.88,0:18:04.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,伟大旅程爷们版 血肉横飞没人管\N{\fs90}Grand Tour for men, splashing all over.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.55,0:18:09.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我勒个槽  -你个王八蛋\N{\fs90}- JEREMY: Bloody hell! - RICHARD: You stupid bastards!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.92,0:18:12.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,我被击中了\N{\fs90}Someone's shot me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.15,0:18:14.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德\N{\fs90}RICHARD: Hammond? Hammond?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.16,0:18:15.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德 收到请回复\N{\fs90}Hammond?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.49,0:18:17.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,你个大猩猩\N{\fs90}Clarkson, you moron.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.39,0:18:18.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德\N{\fs90}Hammond?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.30,0:18:31.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 该诚实就得诚实\N{\fs90}Right, well, I have to be honest,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.24,0:18:33.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,昨天一整天都在浪费时间\N{\fs90}yesterday was a total waste of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.44,0:18:35.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,什么事都没办成\N{\fs90}We achieved nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.58,0:18:39.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,唯一成了的就是射伤了哈蒙德\N{\fs90}All we did achieve was we seem to have wounded Mr Hammond,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.61,0:18:42.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且今天早上 怎么叫他都叫不醒\N{\fs90}who er... well, we couldn't wake him up this morning at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.72,0:18:45.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们今天实在要有长路要赶\N{\fs90}And because we needed to get going, we've a long way to go,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.82,0:18:47.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,于是不得不临场发挥\N{\fs90}we've had to improvise.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.50,0:19:04.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,搞什么鬼\N{\fs90}What the (BLEEP)?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.24,0:19:07.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,这他妈怎么回事\N{\fs90}What the (BLEEP) is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.91,0:19:09.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,混蛋\N{\fs90}You bastards!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.65,0:19:15.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,而在地面上\N{\fs90}Back on the ground,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.02,0:19:19.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,我和詹姆斯也困难重重\N{\fs90}James and I had our own problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.32,0:19:21.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,老天爷啊\N{\fs90}- Oh, God!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.96,0:19:30.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,这段路一定会帮我治愈\N{\fs90}This is very good for the gravel rash
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.96,0:19:35.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,昨天帆伞事故得的皮疹\N{\fs90}that I got... during my parachute accident yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.14,0:19:36.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,好疼\N{\fs90}Oh, that hurts.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.77,0:19:42.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,真希望能下场小雨\N{\fs90}What we could really do with is a rain shower
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.24,0:19:44.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,把这些灰尘压下去\N{\fs90}to dampen this dust down.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.61,0:19:46.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,看起来可能性不大\N{\fs90}JAMES: I think it's unlikely.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.78,0:19:50.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,看起来不像是有要下雨的迹象\N{\fs90}Yeah, there's no evidence that rain is on its way, I would say.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.05,0:19:54.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,过了一会儿 对讲机里说\N{\fs90}JEREMY: Soon, word came over the radio
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.76,0:19:57.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德马上会和我们重新回合\N{\fs90}that Hammond was on his way to rejoin us...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.93,0:20:02.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且他的情绪可能不算最好\N{\fs90}...and that he wasn't in the best of moods.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.40,0:20:04.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,搞什么搞\N{\fs90}What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.60,0:20:07.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,你们什么意思\N{\fs90}What was that about?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.03,0:20:10.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我们不想把你落后面  -你又起不来\N{\fs90}- We didn't want to leave you behind. - You wouldn't wake up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.70,0:20:12.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,啊 对 你不想把我落了\N{\fs90}No, obviously, you didn't want to leave me behind,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.54,0:20:14.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以你们做了合逻辑的事\N{\fs90}so you did the logical thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.14,0:20:16.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,趁我没醒 把我绑在直升机下面\N{\fs90}which is suspend me from a helicopter whilst asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.71,0:20:19.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,-没错啊  -别人也会这么做 是么\N{\fs90}- Yes. - Most people would arrive at the same conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.35,0:20:21.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,当然不是 你们是拿我找乐子\N{\fs90}No, you didn't! You were having a laugh!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.65,0:20:23.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,你不知道刚才有多颠\N{\fs90}Do you realise how rough the first road was
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.72,0:20:25.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,而你不用开啊\N{\fs90}that you haven't had to drive on?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.52,0:20:27.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,而你能乘直升机 我们不行啊\N{\fs90}And you got a helicopter ride, which we haven't had.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.69,0:20:29.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,我要是从那玩意里摔出来\N{\fs90}You wouldn't be laughing and sniggering so much
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.82,0:20:32.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,你们就不会在这嘻嘻哈哈了\N{\fs90}if I'd fallen out of that thing, as I could have done.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.46,0:20:34.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,恩 那样是不可笑\N{\fs90}Well, it wouldn't be funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.19,0:20:35.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,也不对 只是不好玩而已\N{\fs90}No, it just wouldn't be interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.44,0:20:43.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,保护犀牛计划惨败之后\N{\fs90}JEREMY: With the rhino fiasco behind us,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.70,0:20:45.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们继续原来的任务\N{\fs90}we got back to the job in hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.51,0:20:49.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,抵达安哥拉边境\N{\fs90}...which was to reach the Angolan border,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.84,0:20:51.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,以此来证明 沙滩车\N{\fs90}and therefore prove that beach buggies
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.85,0:20:54.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,是无所不能的绝佳机器\N{\fs90}are brilliant go-anywhere machines
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.25,0:20:56.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,而非孩子气的小玩具\N{\fs90}and not just frivolous toys.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.79,0:21:02.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,但今天 这个理论将受到严峻考验\N{\fs90}Today, however, that theory would be seriously tested.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.33,0:21:08.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,老天爷啊\N{\fs90}Oh, for God's sake!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.97,0:21:22.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,啊 震到蛋碎啊\N{\fs90}Ow! Christ on a bike!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.11,0:21:25.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,我不想承认啊 但我好羡慕哈蒙德\N{\fs90}I hate to admit this, but I'm jealous of Hammond.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.98,0:21:30.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,我也想在车上有那套避震\N{\fs90}I wish I'd fitted that suspension on my car.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.18,0:21:34.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,这车全天都这样怎么可能扛得住\N{\fs90}How is this car gonna stand up to this punishment all day?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.96,0:21:39.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 既然这是我自己设计的车\N{\fs90}Well, since it had been designed by me
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.56,0:21:42.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,零部件也都有40岁高龄了\N{\fs90}and made from 40-year-old components,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.20,0:21:44.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,这问题的答案很伤感地在意料之中\N{\fs90}the answer was depressingly predictable.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.37,0:21:50.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,你看 发电机已经从铰链上掉下来了\N{\fs90}The alternator, as you can see, has come off its hinge.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.87,0:21:53.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,这里应该有个螺栓的 掉了\N{\fs90}The bolt's supposed to go in there and it's just come off.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.04,0:21:57.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,那螺栓 应该在后面 160公里的某处\N{\fs90}And the bolt, well, that's somewhere back there, 100 miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.59,0:22:08.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,好了 我的发电机现在靠螺丝起子挂着\N{\fs90}So, my alternator is now held on with a screwdriver
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.29,0:22:10.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,我亲手锤进去的\N{\fs90}that I've hammered into place.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.49,0:22:12.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,效果非凡\N{\fs90}And we're running well.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.63,0:22:20.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,我真有点束手无策了\N{\fs90}Oh. I don't know what I'm gonna do about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.63,0:22:22.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,风扇皮带没了\N{\fs90}but I don't have a fan belt on there.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.11,0:22:28.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,又有问题了\N{\fs90}I've got a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.24,0:22:32.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,才走了8公里 又掉了个风扇皮带\N{\fs90}Another five miles, another fan belt.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.68,0:22:34.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,我要两件紧身衣才行\N{\fs90}I'm gonna need a pair of tights.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.12,0:22:39.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,不光我这样\N{\fs90}And it wasn't just me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.72,0:22:43.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,这里 这里 点火开关 都检查过了\N{\fs90}I've been through all of that, all of that, the ignition cut-out switch.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.16,0:22:45.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,但机器就像中邪一样\N{\fs90}I've got some weird gremlin.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.16,0:22:48.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,这路要把车给拆了\N{\fs90}JEREMY: This road is just shaking these cars to pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.77,0:22:54.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,当然了 杰里米一心认定\N{\fs90}JAMES: Naturally, Jeremy decided that the only way
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.47,0:22:56.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,唯一能让车保持完整的方法\N{\fs90}of keeping his car in one piece
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.44,0:22:59.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是开得飞快\N{\fs90}was to drive very quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.27,0:23:03.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的理想速度是2800转\N{\fs90}My optimum speed is 2,800 rpm,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.34,0:23:05.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是唯一工作的仪表了\N{\fs90}that being my only dial, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.71,0:23:08.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,这样 我就能跳过坑洼了\N{\fs90}That way, I'm skipping over the top of the ridges.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.25,0:23:12.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,不幸的是 这速度下\N{\fs90}Unfortunately, at this speed,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.59,0:23:14.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的V8每50公里\N{\fs90}my V8 was emptying the petrol tank
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.92,0:23:17.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,就把油箱喝干了\N{\fs90}every 31 miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.19,0:23:20.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,而我们在露营店里忘记买的一样东西\N{\fs90}And one of the items we'd forgotten to buy at the camping shop
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.53,0:23:22.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是漏斗\N{\fs90}was a funnel.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.86,0:23:25.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,好了 风小了点 来吧\N{\fs90}Right, wind's dropped. Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.83,0:23:26.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,给我喝\N{\fs90}Drink!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.27,0:23:30.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,绝对安全\N{\fs90}This is completely safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.50,0:23:33.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,有些汽油 嗷我的好姑姑诶\N{\fs90}Some of the petrol is... Oh, my giddy aunt!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.38,0:23:40.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,路况越来越糟\N{\fs90}The roads are getting worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.01,0:23:44.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,虽然路途艰辛\N{\fs90}Even though the going was appalling...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.25,0:23:49.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,但沙滩车们 很神奇的\N{\fs90}...the beach buggies, amazingly,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.29,0:23:52.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,多多少少还保持完整\N{\fs90}were, more or less, still in one piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.09,0:23:56.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,不过 随着坑洼不断\N{\fs90}However, as the relentless pounding wore on,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.90,0:24:00.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,这话在詹姆斯那就没用了\N{\fs90}the same could not be said of James.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.24,0:24:06.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,老天啊\N{\fs90}Oh, my God!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.98,0:24:11.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,讲真我骨头都要碎了\N{\fs90}Honestly, my bones are going to shatter.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.09,0:24:25.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,我受够了\N{\fs90}I've had enough of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.23,0:24:31.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,我正试着把前避震调软\N{\fs90}What I'm doing is I'm trying to soften up the front suspension,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.53,0:24:33.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后把轮胎也弄软\N{\fs90}and I'm gonna soften the tyres as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.53,0:24:35.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,我在这里动动手脚\N{\fs90}I've done quite a bit under here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.14,0:24:38.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后把轮胎里的气放掉些\N{\fs90}Now I'm going to let a bit of air out of the tyres.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.94,0:24:42.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,效果立竿见影啊\N{\fs90}JAMES: This made a huge difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.35,0:24:50.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,简直垃圾\N{\fs90}This is rubbish!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.55,0:24:54.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,别颠了\N{\fs90}Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.62,0:24:59.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,但根本停不下来\N{\fs90}But it didn't stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.36,0:25:00.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,一路颠着\N{\fs90}It went on...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.20,0:25:03.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,颠着\N{\fs90}...and on.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.67,0:25:07.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,那天 我开了560公里\N{\fs90}That day, I did 350 miles,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.60,0:25:10.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,每公里都浸淫着痛苦\N{\fs90}and every single one of them was filled with pain,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.84,0:25:12.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,交织着灰尘与不幸\N{\fs90}dust and misery.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.58,0:25:19.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以 第二天早上\N{\fs90}And that's why , the following morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.58,0:25:22.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,我想到了个激进的计划\N{\fs90}I came up with a radical plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.75,0:25:27.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,别在路上开 开在路旁\N{\fs90}Don't drive on the road, drive near it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.09,0:25:28.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,我在路旁开了一小段\N{\fs90}I did a bit alongside the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.76,0:25:30.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,虽然只有半公里\N{\fs90}Admittedly only half a kilometre,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.76,0:25:32.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,但简直天差地别\N{\fs90}but it was bliss by comparison.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.46,0:25:34.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,就像开在新铺装好的银石赛道上\N{\fs90}It was like driving on a freshly resurfaced Silverstone.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.96,0:25:37.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们不需要离开路好几公里\N{\fs90}We don't have to stray miles from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.20,0:25:39.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,我同意 这会很纯 我们会变成骷髅骨架的\N{\fs90}I agree, that would be foolish, cos we could just end up as skeletons.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.90,0:25:42.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,不过 说真的 我痛苦极了\N{\fs90}But, honestly, it's agony in mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.64,0:25:46.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,头颈疼 头疼 恨死了\N{\fs90}I've got neck ache, headache. I hate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.34,0:25:49.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,好 我跟你讲 哈蒙德 我为什么喜欢他的计划\N{\fs90}Right, I tell you what, Hammond. I tell you why I like his idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.61,0:25:54.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果是平地越野 我们会更舒服\N{\fs90}If it is smooth off-road, it's more comfortable for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.25,0:25:58.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果情况糟糕 我们就怪他\N{\fs90}If it's hopeless out there, we can blame him.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.22,0:25:59.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,很公平\N{\fs90}Fair enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.12,0:26:04.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,决定之后 我们就离开路面\N{\fs90}JEREMY: With that settled, we left the road
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.79,0:26:07.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,一路开进船长高速\N{\fs90}and set out on Highway May.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.30,0:26:15.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,肯定詹姆斯一点 确实比路上平顺\N{\fs90}I'll give James one thing, it is smoother than the road,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.64,0:26:18.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,但我速度只有5\N{\fs90}but I am doing 3 mph.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.01,0:26:20.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,我说 我喜欢越野 真的\N{\fs90}I mean, yeah, I like off-roading, I do,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.91,0:26:25.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,但 这真的不快啊 对吧\N{\fs90}but... this isn't exactly quicker, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.11,0:26:27.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,可惜 过了一小会\N{\fs90}JEREMY: Sadly, a short while later,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.08,0:26:30.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们连平顺路面都没了\N{\fs90}we didn't even have smooth going for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.86,0:26:36.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦 漂亮\N{\fs90}Oh, spiffing.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.93,0:26:41.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯 我希望你开心啊\N{\fs90}James, I hope you're happy with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.29,0:26:44.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,要这都比原来好 那之前得要多糟\N{\fs90}How bad must it have been for him if this is better?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.03,0:26:52.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,啊 老天 这人怎么这么蠢\N{\fs90}Oh, God al-bloody-mighty! What an idiot that man is!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.11,0:26:54.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,是啊 这可没那么颠了\N{\fs90}Yeah, this is a lot less bumpy.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.51,0:26:55.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,老天\N{\fs90}Oh, Christ!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.58,0:27:01.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,这更好 真的么\N{\fs90}Is this better? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.69,0:27:06.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,别叫了\N{\fs90}Stop moaning!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.76,0:27:14.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德 我整个油门都掉下来了\N{\fs90}JEREMY: Hammond, my entire throttle assembly has disintegrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.53,0:27:17.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,我不懂 但我确定这路脱不了干系\N{\fs90}RICHARD: I can't see why. I'm sure this is all helping it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.23,0:27:19.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,路上绝对没问题的\N{\fs90}JEREMY: Perfectly all right on the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.17,0:27:20.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,是啊 我就不懂为啥越来越多人\N{\fs90}Yeah, I don't know why more people
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.70,0:27:23.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,不把车开在公路上\N{\fs90}don't drive their cars on the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.77,0:27:26.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,别让这风景给你的设计失误背锅\N{\fs90}Stop blaming your failures on the scenery.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.14,0:27:29.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,他胯部的每根骨头\N{\fs90}Every bone in his crotch...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.74,0:27:31.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,我都想打碎\N{\fs90}that's what I'm gonna break.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.48,0:27:33.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,每 一 根\N{\fs90}Every single one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.98,0:27:36.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,接着 让人难以置信的是\N{\fs90}And then, if it were at all possible,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.48,0:27:38.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,船长旅行社的路线更糟了\N{\fs90}May Tours got even worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.85,0:27:44.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,天啊 这灰\N{\fs90}Oh! Oh, God! The dust! Agh!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.09,0:27:48.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们是开到星际迷航的特效里了么\N{\fs90}What is this Star Trek special effect we've arrived in?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.13,0:27:52.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,天啊\N{\fs90}Oh, my God!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.74,0:27:58.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,我是游过了灰啊 真的是游过去的\N{\fs90}I am swimming through dust. I'm actually swimming in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.74,0:28:02.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,天啊 天啊\N{\fs90}Oh, dear, oh, dear!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.58,0:28:05.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们开进的东西叫做浮土\N{\fs90}JAMES: We had driven into something called fesh fesh,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.88,0:28:08.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,像滑石粉一样细的沙\N{\fs90}a sand as fine as talcum powder.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.78,0:28:10.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦草\N{\fs90}Oh, shite!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.82,0:28:14.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,这让Ali G更怒了\N{\fs90}And this had made Ali G even more cross.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.96,0:28:19.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,我什么都看不到了 我得要\N{\fs90}I can't see a bloody thing now. I've got to...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.79,0:28:22.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,都没法找到詹姆斯然后宰了他了\N{\fs90}I can't even find James May to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.37,0:28:31.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,好了 发动机炸锅了 我困住了\N{\fs90}JEREMY: OK, the engine's boiling and I'm stuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.20,0:28:33.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,电子系统全乱套了\N{\fs90}All my electrics have gone haywire
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.47,0:28:35.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,我 还在试着把车子发动 电池不行了\N{\fs90}My... It's still trying to turn the motor over. The battery's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.04,0:28:37.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,你困住了么 詹姆斯\N{\fs90}Are you stuck, James?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.81,0:28:39.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,呃\N{\fs90}Er...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.95,0:28:43.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,我猜我困住了\N{\fs90}I think I'm stuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.65,0:28:45.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,干得漂亮 詹姆斯\N{\fs90}Well done, James.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.79,0:28:47.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,你走了大家都好\N{\fs90}Improved our lot no end.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.55,0:28:49.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以情况就是\N{\fs90}So the situation is...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.36,0:28:51.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德的车坏了 你困住了\N{\fs90}Hammond has broken his car, you're stuck,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.99,0:28:54.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的过热了\N{\fs90}and mine's overheated.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.13,0:28:57.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们是不是该说 詹姆斯 你的主意蠢透了\N{\fs90}Are we going to say, James, that your idea was stupid?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.37,0:29:00.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,是蠢透了\N{\fs90}It was stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.00,0:29:07.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,连固执中士都承认战败\N{\fs90}JEREMY: With even Sergeant Stubborn admitting defeat,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.14,0:29:09.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,是时候认输了\N{\fs90}it was time to throw in the towel.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.48,0:29:13.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以我们把自己安排妥当 在河里洗了个澡\N{\fs90}So we got ourselves sorted out, got a wash in the river
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.58,0:29:17.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,回到了路上\N{\fs90}and headed back to the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.45,0:29:20.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,你瞧 新烫好的亚麻衬衫\N{\fs90}There you go. Freshly ironed linen shirt
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.35,0:29:24.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有和我沙滩车同款肩章\N{\fs90}with epaulettes that matches my beach buggy.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.83,0:29:26.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,乔瓦尼烫的\N{\fs90}Ironed by Giovanni.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.53,0:29:31.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,不管别的\N{\fs90}Despite everything,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.06,0:29:34.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们的沙滩车的1600公里旅途\N{\fs90}our beach buggies had covered 750 miles
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.70,0:29:36.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,已经完成了1200公里\N{\fs90}of our 1,000-mile journey,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.90,0:29:39.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,而我们现在已经深入北纳米比亚的\N{\fs90}and we were now well into the tribal regions
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.57,0:29:41.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,原始部落领地\N{\fs90}of northern Namibia...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.84,0:29:45.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,教科书般的非洲\N{\fs90}...which is picture-book Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.85,0:29:50.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,言语已经无法形容这里的美了\N{\fs90}Well, this is all a bit too beautiful for words along here.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.88,0:29:52.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,瞧瞧这\N{\fs90}Look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.95,0:29:54.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,纳米比亚部落 我喜欢\N{\fs90}Tribal Namibia, I like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.86,0:30:05.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们所在的地方 完全是\N{\fs90}Where we are now, it's genuinely...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.40,0:30:09.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,怎么说好 未受玷污的\N{\fs90}Well, what would you say, "unspoiled"? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.44,0:30:11.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,人们过着和数千年以前\N{\fs90}People do live the lives
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.77,0:30:14.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,完全一样的生活\N{\fs90}they've led here for thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.24,0:30:18.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,不好\N{\fs90}Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.08,0:30:21.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,不好 我车不行了\N{\fs90}Oh, no! I'm dying!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.92,0:30:24.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,烦人的是 詹姆斯梅的远足\N{\fs90}Annoyingly, the James May excursion
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.65,0:30:27.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,对我车的损坏远糟于我预期\N{\fs90}had caused more damage than I'd realised.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.29,0:30:30.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,噢 现在这里卡住了\N{\fs90}Oh, now this is stuck on.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.99,0:30:32.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,蠢货\N{\fs90}Oh, bugger.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.73,0:30:35.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,接着 代替道路救援服务的\N{\fs90}Then, instead of the breakdown-recovery service,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.86,0:30:38.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,一群无上装妇女来了\N{\fs90}some topless ladies arrived...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.30,0:30:41.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,你们好\N{\fs90}RICHARD: Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.83,0:30:45.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,这让我不知道该把视线往哪放\N{\fs90}...which made knowing where to look a bit difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.11,0:30:53.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,呃 全心干活啊 理查德\N{\fs90}Erm... Concentrate on the job, Richard.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.35,0:30:57.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,这不寻常啊\N{\fs90}This is unusual.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.52,0:30:59.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,和平时道路救援相比的话\N{\fs90}I mean, normally the AA would have done.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.59,0:31:02.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,谢谢啦\N{\fs90}Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.96,0:31:05.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,真棒\N{\fs90}Very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.46,0:31:08.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦还没完\N{\fs90}Oh, there's more.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.24,0:31:20.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,我也在休养船长旅行社造成的创伤\N{\fs90}JEREMY: I, too, was nursing wounds as a result of May Tours.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.27,0:31:21.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,我好像\N{\fs90}I do seem to have lost...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.54,0:31:25.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,缺了一个缸\N{\fs90}...one of my cylinders somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.21,0:31:26.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,我在开V7啊\N{\fs90}I'm driving a V7.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.25,0:31:32.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,基本上 这就是喷天万能车了\N{\fs90}Basically, this is now Spitty Spitty Bang Bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.79,0:31:35.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以 在午餐休息时 理查德和我\N{\fs90}So, at the lunch stop, Richard and I decided
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.96,0:31:37.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,决定开始报复梅先生\N{\fs90}to get our revenge on Mr May.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.67,0:31:50.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,怎么啦\N{\fs90}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.97,0:31:52.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,你... 放哪儿去了\N{\fs90}You've put... Where's...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.71,0:31:55.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,太糟心了\N{\fs90}That is disturbing.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.21,0:31:56.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,更糟心的是 我的原版古董大众档把\N{\fs90}What's annoying is, what have you done
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.98,0:31:59.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,你把它怎么样了\N{\fs90}with my original vintage VW gear knob?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.21,0:32:01.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 这是好消息\N{\fs90}Ah, well, no, good news on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.41,0:32:03.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,乔瓦尼已经把你的原厂档把\N{\fs90}Giovanni has posted your original gear lever
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.62,0:32:05.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,寄到你伦敦的家里了\N{\fs90}back to your address in London.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.09,0:32:06.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,-是吗   -特快专递\N{\fs90}- Has he? -Special delivery.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.75,0:32:09.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,你什么毛病啊 这太恶心了\N{\fs90}What is the matter with you? That's really offensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.99,0:32:12.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,你这样是歧视男人\N{\fs90}Well, I think that's a bit sexist.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.56,0:32:15.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,才没有 我为啥要用一根假JJ开车\N{\fs90}No, it's not. Why would I want to drive with a rubber penis?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.43,0:32:17.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,不知道啊 可能你是个变态\N{\fs90}I don't know. I think you're weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.00,0:32:27.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,休息结束 我们重新上路\N{\fs90}With our break over, we got back on the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.67,0:32:31.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,美国观众们 船长正开着一辆手动”屌”\N{\fs90}For our American viewers, James May is driving a dick-shift.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.45,0:32:36.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且不仅是船长的”裆把儿”\N{\fs90}And it wasn't just James's knob
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.45,0:32:38.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,一直在逗我们笑\N{\fs90}that was keeping us amused.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.38,0:32:40.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,午餐的时候还听到一件事\N{\fs90}There was something else we'd learned over lunch
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.65,0:32:42.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,更加好笑\N{\fs90}that was even funnier.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.82,0:32:46.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,船长的油箱上有个洞 或者是裂了\N{\fs90}James May's fuel tank has a hole in it, or it's split.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.16,0:32:49.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,他开的是一枚定时炸弹\N{\fs90}He's driving a bomb.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.23,0:32:52.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在形势很紧张\N{\fs90}It's a tense moment, this.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.03,0:32:55.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,就像足球赛快结束时比分1-1\N{\fs90}It's like the end of a football match when it's 1-1.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.87,0:32:57.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,你只管开 你知道他要炸\N{\fs90}You're driving along, you know he's gonna blow up,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.04,0:33:00.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是不知道啥时候炸\N{\fs90}you just don't know when.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.44,0:33:02.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,报纸登出来不好看吧\N{\fs90}RICHARD: It's not gonna read well in the papers.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.41,0:33:06.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,"詹姆斯梅死于沙滩车爆炸 手中握着假JJ"\N{\fs90}"James May died in an exploding beach buggy, holding a rubber penis."
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.55,0:33:09.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,噢闭嘴吧\N{\fs90}Oh, shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.58,0:33:10.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的天\N{\fs90}Jeez!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.36,0:33:18.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,正中面门\N{\fs90}JAMES: Oh! In the face!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.79,0:33:24.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,当船长的油箱见底时\N{\fs90}JEREMY: Once James's fuel tank had run low enough,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.60,0:33:26.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们停在了一个小村子里\N{\fs90}we pulled over in a small village
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.40,0:33:28.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,他可以做些修补\N{\fs90}so he could make some repairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.84,0:33:35.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为风往那儿吹 所以爆炸的火球也朝那儿\N{\fs90}Well, the wind's blowing that way, so the fireball will go up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.64,0:33:37.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,等下他死的时候 一下子就完了\N{\fs90}It'll be sudden, won't it, when he goes?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.08,0:33:39.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,是啊 "轰"的一声\N{\fs90}Yeah. It's "woompf."
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.21,0:33:40.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后一阵静寂\N{\fs90}"Woompf," then a bit of quiet,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.45,0:33:42.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后各种肉渣掉下来\N{\fs90}and then... as all bits come down.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.18,0:33:43.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,对\N{\fs90}JEREMY: Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.92,0:33:46.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,油箱的裂缝在这里\N{\fs90}Here's the split in the tank.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.15,0:33:48.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,-用上这个  -你好\N{\fs90}- Apply this. - Oh, hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.89,0:33:51.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,你知道我们一直在说这路有多烂吧，哈蒙德\N{\fs90}You know we've been saying how bad the roads are, Hammond?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.76,0:33:53.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\fs90}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.39,0:33:56.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,烂到能搞坏一辆搞不坏的车\N{\fs90}They're bad enough to kill an un-killable car.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.80,0:33:58.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,这场景也算可怕吧\N{\fs90}That's kind of a terrifying sight, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.73,0:34:03.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,是啊 我这辈子从来没见过\N{\fs90}I know. I've never seen that before in my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.14,0:34:05.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,一辆报废的丰田皮卡\N{\fs90}A dead Toyota pickup truck.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.61,0:34:09.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,船长的油箱补好了\N{\fs90}With James's tank bodged,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.58,0:34:12.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们鼓足劲想多跑几里路\N{\fs90}we knuckled down to getting some miles under our belt.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.42,0:34:17.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,然而这天剩余时间里\N{\fs90}And for the rest of the day,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.35,0:34:20.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,唯一有燃料问题的人是我\N{\fs90}the only person with petrol issues was me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.93,0:34:30.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,好了 加满了 我又能跑个50公里\N{\fs90}Right. Refuelled, so I'm good now for 31 miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.47,0:34:36.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,一天结束 我们有了不少进展\N{\fs90}By the end of the day, we'd made good progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.27,0:34:38.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,而当我们停下来扎营时\N{\fs90}And when we stopped to make camp...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.14,0:34:40.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,乔瓦尼他妈的去哪儿了\N{\fs90}Where the bloody hell's Giovanni?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.04,0:34:44.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们离终点只有不到160公里了\N{\fs90}...we were less than 100 miles from the finish line.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.58,0:34:47.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以晚饭后 我们决定讨论一番\N{\fs90}So, after supper, we decided to have a conversation -
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.35,0:34:48.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,不对 争论一番\N{\fs90}well, argument -
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.95,0:34:52.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,关于谁造的沙滩车最好\N{\fs90}about who'd built the best beach buggy.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.59,0:34:56.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,重点是 你造的不是沙滩车\N{\fs90}The point is, yours isn't a beach buggy.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.72,0:34:57.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我的车  -嗯\N{\fs90}- My car? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.06,0:34:59.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的车不仅有沙滩车的壳\N{\fs90}Apart from having a beach buggy's body
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.59,0:35:02.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有一颗跳动的沙滩车之心\N{\fs90}and the beating, pulsating heart of a beach buggy,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.23,0:35:03.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,也就是甲壳虫的引擎\N{\fs90}namely a Beetle engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.56,0:35:05.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,我看着你的车就想\N{\fs90}I look at yours and go,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.30,0:35:06.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,"这看起来都不像一辆沙滩车"\N{\fs90}"That doesn't even look like a beach buggy."
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.03,0:35:09.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,像啊 它就是沙滩车啊\N{\fs90}It does and it is! It's a beach buggy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.34,0:35:11.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是升级版 但保留了沙滩车的灵魂\N{\fs90}Enhanced, but in the spirit of beach buggying.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.37,0:35:14.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,-根本不是  -杰里米 你的车是...怪物\N{\fs90}- It isn't. - Jeremy, yours is... a freak.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.97,0:35:18.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果在100年前 它会被拿去展览\N{\fs90}Had it existed 100 years ago, it would have been exhibited.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.18,0:35:21.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,人们会从大老远来围观 小孩子会透过帘子偷看\N{\fs90}People would come from miles and children would peak at it through curtains.
